# P1X Gemini Capsule

## Low-tech, High-life
In true low-tech fasion I'm hosting this micro capsule from a €1 microcomputer powered by a solar energy!
=> capsule-live.jpg Image of the capsule in its natural environment ;) [29.2KB]

Solar-powered means that it is ON-LINE only when there is enough sun thru the day to recharge the battery.

> It's a proof-of-concept an a little poligon. My end goal is to have small, cheap and realiable device to host gemini capsules in the rural areas.

## Hardware List

* 🖳 ESP-01S ~€1
* 🌞 Solar cell 0,7W/5,5V €4.10
* 🂠 Lipol charger TP4056 1S 3,7V  €1.37
* 🔋 EMAX 1s 450mAh battery ~$9 (I got mine from a drone)

## Hardware Specs

### Specifications of 🖳 microcontroller
* ESP-01S
* 80MHz RISC 32-bit CPU: Tensilica Diamond Standard 106Micro
* 32KiB RAM RAM: 32 KiB instruction, 80 KiB user data
* 1MB FLASH (~420KB for user data)
* WiFI 2.4GHz
* 220mA in peek power usage
* 3.3V / 250mA

### Specifications of 🌞 solar cell
* Power: 0.7 W
* Output voltage: 5,5 V
* The dimensions of the plate: 95 x 95 x 3 mm

### Specification of 🂠 TP4056
* Power supply voltage: (microUSB or IN connectors) from 4.5 V to 5.5 V
* Charging voltage: 4,2 V
* Maximum charging current: 1 A
* Module dimensions 26 x 18 mm

### Specification of 🔋 battery
* Voltage: 1s 4.35v HV
* Capacity: 450 mAh
* Discharge rating: 80c/160c

